content: She reports continued soft tissue swelling, particularly when her hand is more active. She is inquiring about the normalcy of this swelling.  She notes significant improvement in sensation, with hypersensitivity experienced two weeks prior now resolved.  The increased sensitivity had been present for about a week before improving.  The swelling and sensitivity impact her ability to use her hand actively.
title: History of Present Illness

content: Incision well healed, very minimal scar, no firmness to the scar. Excellent range of motion, full tight fist without pain , able to get hand flat on the table, there is a very slight extension lag, less than 5 degrees when compared to her baseline . Hyperextension , sensation decreased but improving to the on one of the digit.
title: Musculoskeletal

content: Right upper extremity Skin is intact.
